ure also asserts, for $k gg\\log |G|$, that the\ncutoff time should depend only on $k$ and $|G|$. This was verified for all\nAbelian groups. Our result shows that this is not the case for $U_{p,d}$: the\ncutoff time depends on $k$, $|U_{p,d}| = p^{d(d-1)/2}$ and\n$|U_{p,d}^\\mathrm{ab}|=p^{d-1}$.\n  We also show that all but $o(|U_{p,d}|)$ of the elements of $U_{p,d}$ lie at\ngraph distance $M \\pm o(M)$ from the identity, where $M$ is the minimal radius\nof a ball in $\\mathbb Z^k$ of cardinality $|U_{p,d}^\\mathrm{ab}| = p^{d-1}$.\nFinally, we show that the diameter is also asymptotically $M$ when $k \\gtrsim\n\\log |U_{p,d}^\\textrm{ab}|$ and $d\\asymp1$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Nov 2019 17:22:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 4 Feb 2021 18:57:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-05"}
