 FSRQ is located marginally below this\nregion, while two FSRQs lie above the line $\\mathcal{T}=2/3$, i.e. they are\neven more noisy than white noise. The BL Lac candidates are characterised by\nhigher $\\mathcal{A}$ values than FSRQs, i.e. $0.71\\pm 0.06$ and $0.29\\pm 0.05$,\nrespectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 8 Nov 2019 05:58:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-11"}
